==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic, corresponding to ''[[eln]]'' + ''[[boga]]''.  Cognate with Middle Dutch [[elleboghe]] (Dutch [[elleboog]]), Old High German [[elinbogo]] (German [[Ellenbogen]]), Old Norse [[ǫllnbogi]].

